Buffett Confident Son Could Lead Board, CEO Tells ‘60 Minutes’

-- B y   P e t e r   E i c h e n b a u m
-- 
2011-12-12T01:44:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-12/buffett-confident-son-could-lead-board-ceo-tells-60-minutes-.html
Warren Buffett , chairman and chief
executive officer of  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A) , told CBS program
“60 Minutes” that he’s confident in the ability of his son
Howard to lead the board.  “He knows plenty about the business in terms of the values
of the business,” the elder Buffett, 81, said in the interview
broadcast today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Eichenbaum in New York at 
 peichenbaum@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at 
 dkraut2@bloomberg.net  